gomodel:SYNGO_340  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: C1QBP was found tightly associated with docked synaptic vesicles and not with free synaptic vesicles in this proteomic study. It is 1.4-fold enriched in VGLUT1- over VGAT-containing presynapses. In the literature the protein was described as cytoplasmic component, mitochondrial protein and extracellular matrix component.\n\n20/3/2017 Pim\n- Because enriched in AZ and not in free SV protein is presumably localized to the AZ, and not in co-purifying SVs.. Experimental description: To isolate docking complexes from rat brain, we first prepared synaptosomes and subjected them to limited proteolysis to dissociate pre- and postsynaptic membranes (Figure 1A). p. 286" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" ;
        dc:date           "2017-03-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_340" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

